No one is braver
than the rain in June
It hides its longing drops
to the flowering tree
No one is wiser
than the rain in June
It erases its hesitant steps
on the road
No one is more clever
than the rain in June
It leaves the unspoken words
to be absorbed by the roots of the flower tree
I want to love you simply
with words that are not said
wood to fire that makes it ash
I want to love you simply
with signs that are not delivered
cloud to rain that makes it gone
What is fleeting is time.
We are eternal picking up second by second,
stringing them like flowers
until one day
we forget for what
"But, what is fleeting is time, right?" you ask.
We are eternal.
One day,
My body will be no more,
But in these verses of poetry,
I will not let you alone.
One day,
My voice will not be heard,
But among these lines of poetry.
I will still tease you,
One day,
My dream will not be known,
But between these letters of poetry,
I will not tire of looking for you.
